## Smoke pipeline summary

### What worked out of the box

- `docker compose up -d --wait` — all three services (db, redis, minio) healthy via compose-side healthchecks, minio-init bucket creation ran cleanly
- `migrate` — all migrations applied first try after fixing `INSTALLED_APPS`
- `/admin/login/`, `/accounts/login/` — both 200
- `/healthz` → `ok`, `/readyz` → `ready` — exact string match passed
- Celery worker started and connected to Redis
- Bolt settings assertions — `admin` stripped, `ROOT_URLCONF = config.urls_bolt`, `TEMPLATES = []` all passed
- `docker build --target prod` — succeeded; Python 3.12.13 confirmed; `uv` not in runtime image

### What broke and fixes applied

| Issue | Fix |
|---|---|
| Port 5432/6379/9000/9001 taken by other projects | Remapped compose ports to 5433/6380/9002/9003 |
| `INSTALLED_APPS` had `health_check.db`, `.cache` etc. — not valid in django-health-check v4.4 | Replaced with single `"health_check"` entry |
| `AXES_LOCKOUT_CALLABLE = "axes.helpers.lockout_response"` — that function doesn't exist in axes v8 | Removed setting; default behavior is correct |
| `config/urls_bolt.py` had no `urlpatterns` — Django URLconf check failed | Added `urlpatterns: list = []` |
| Bolt port 8001 still held by first crashed attempt | `lsof -ti :8001 \| xargs kill -9` before retry |
| Pyright scanning `.venv/**` (11k errors) | Added `.venv/**` to pyright `exclude` |
| Pyright: `request.user` not narrowed past `AnonymousUser` | `cast(User, request.user)` in GDPR views |
| Pyright: `User.id` unknown (django-stubs uses `.pk`) | Changed `user.id` → `user.pk` in bolt API handler |
| `collectstatic` in Dockerfile fails without live S3 | `|| true` already in CMD; build still completes |

### Suggested skill changes

1. **`django-health-check` INSTALLED_APPS pattern**: The skill should generate `"health_check"` (single entry) instead of the old `health_check.db / .cache / .contrib.*` pattern — the v4.x API is class-based, not multi-app.
2. **Port collision handling**: When generating docker-compose, note that `5432/6379/9000` are commonly occupied in multi-project environments — add a comment or use project-specific offsets by default.
3. **Pyright exclude**: Always add `.venv/**` to pyright `exclude` — without it pyright checks all installed packages and generates thousands of false positives.
4. **`AXES_LOCKOUT_CALLABLE`**: Remove this setting from the django-axes template — `axes.helpers.lockout_response` doesn't exist in v8+.
5. **`urls_bolt.py`**: Always emit `urlpatterns: list = []` even if empty, not just a bare `path` import.
6. **`User.pk` vs `User.id`**: django-stubs doesn't expose `.id` on `User` — the skill should use `.pk` in any generated User serialization code.
